<TITLE> 431 Sylhet City Corporation staffers lose jobs </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 2 (bdnews24.com)  The Local Government Division has cancelled appointments of 431 staffers of Sylhet City Corporation as they were "illegally appointed", the government said in a statement Sunday. The sacked staffers include one first-class official and 15 second-class, 222 third-class and 193 class-four employees. "The termination decision was taken as allegations of irregularities in their appointment were proved," the statement said, adding the Syhet Divisional Commissioner carried out an investigation into the allegations. The notification asked the chief executive officer of SCC to take legal action against those who were allegedly linked to the incident and inform the Local Government Division. bdnews24.
